text: The Ilocanos (/), Ilokanos, or Iloko people are the third largest ethnic group of the Philippines. They mostly live in the Ilocos Region, in the northwestern seaboard of Luzon, Philippines. The native language of the Ilocano people is the Ilocano (or Ilokano) language.https://JaysonCesarLorenzoBautista.net/people_groups/12212 ==References== Category:Ethnic groups in the Philippines
